{"id":6,"name":"EV006","note":"","pages":[{"conditions":{"actorId":1,"actorValid":false,"itemId":1,"itemValid":false,"selfSwitchCh":"A","selfSwitchValid":false,"switch1Id":1,"switch1Valid":false,"switch2Id":1,"switch2Valid":false,"variableId":1,"variableValid":false,"variableValue":0},"directionFix":false,"image":{"tileId":0,"characterName":"!Flame","direction":8,"pattern":0,"characterIndex":6},"list":[{"code":357,"indent":0,"parameters":["VisuMZ_2_QuestSystem","TrackerShowHide","Tracker: Show/Hide Window",{"Show:eval":"false"}]},{"code":657,"indent":0,"parameters":["Show/Hide? = false"]},{"code":118,"indent":0,"parameters":["Tutorial_Menu"]},{"code":101,"indent":0,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":0,"parameters":["Select one of the options to learn more about the game."]},{"code":102,"indent":0,"parameters":[["Stats","Equipment","Cancel"],2,-1,2,0]},{"code":402,"indent":0,"parameters":[0,"Stats"]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[2,"JustBlack",0,0,0,0,100,100,255,0]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_apoints0",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["\\c[17]Ability Points\\c[0] are awarded to you upon leveling up. Keep an eye on your \\c[3]A.Points\\c[0] amount - whenever you have more than 0, it means you can spend them to boost your stats."]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["In short, battle stats are important for ensuring your character is strong and can win battles. Jutsus also scale with any one or combination of these stats (usually attack or chakra attack)."]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_apoints1",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["Inside the submenu, you can select 'Allocate' to parse through each stat of the character and spend your ability points to increase them individually (you can either click on each stat or use your keyboard's left/right arrow keys). Note that the 'Cost/Available' indicates the cost of ability points for leveling up the selected stat as well as the remaining ability points you have."]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_apoints2",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["Generally, leveling up a specific stat will eventually increase the cost of ability points to continue doing so. In this example, after spending enough ability points on HP, it now costs 2 ability points to increase HP."]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_apoints3",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["Once you allocate your ability points, you can select 'Finish' or simply exit the menu. To refund all your points and start from zero, you can select 'Revert'."]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_apoints4",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["Reverting will simply refund all your allocated ability points back to you, you technically won't lose anything by doing it - just remember to re-allocate your refunded points!"]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":235,"indent":1,"parameters":[2]},{"code":235,"indent":1,"parameters":[3]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":119,"indent":1,"parameters":["Tutorial_Menu"]},{"code":0,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":402,"indent":0,"parameters":[1,"Equipment"]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[2,"JustBlack",0,0,0,0,100,100,255,0]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_equipment_0",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["\\c[17]Equipment\\c[0] can be found in this game by defeating enemies, finding it in the world, completing certain quests, and more. It is a good way to boost your character's battle stats."]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_equipment_1",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["There are five types of equipment: weapons, head armor, body armor, boots, and accessories."]},{"code":221,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":231,"indent":1,"parameters":[3,"tutorial_equipment_2",0,0,120,-24,30,30,255,0]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":222,"indent":1,"parameters":[]},{"code":230,"indent":1,"parameters":[10]},{"code":101,"indent":1,"parameters":["",0,0,2,""]},{"code":401,"indent":1,"parameters":["The easiest way to equip your armor is to simply clic